<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<xsd:schema xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <xsd:element name="ArcConfig">
    <xsd:annotation><xsd:documentation>Preliminary XML schema for a client user configuration file</xsd:documentation></xsd:annotation>
    <xsd:complexType>
      <xsd:all>
        <xsd:element name="AliasList" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
              AliasList specifies a list of alias.
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
          <xsd:complexType>
            <xsd:sequence>
              <xsd:element name="Alias" maxOccurs="unbounded">
                <xsd:annotation>
                  <xsd:documentation xml:lang="EN">
A alias is a short hand notation identifier of one or multiple URL(s) pointing
to either a computing or index service(s). The <attribute>name</attribute>
attribute specifies the name of the alias, while the <element>Alias</element>
element may either contain one or multiple <element>URL</element> element(s) or
one or multiple <element>AliasRef</element> element(s).
                  </xsd:documentation>
                </xsd:annotation>
                <xsd:complexType>
                  <xsd:sequence>
                    <xsd:choice>
                      <xsd:element name="AliasRef" type="xsd:string" maxOccurs="unbounded">
                        <xsd:annotation>
                          <xsd:documentation>
This element is a reference to a previous defined alias.
                          </xsd:documentation>
                        </xsd:annotation>
                      </xsd:element>
                      <xsd:element ref="URL"/>
                    </xsd:choice>
                  </xsd:sequence>
                  <xsd:attribute name="name" type="xsd:string" use="required"/>
                </xsd:complexType>
              </xsd:element>
            </xsd:sequence>
          </xsd:complexType>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="DefaultServices" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:complexType>
            <xsd:sequence>
              <xsd:element name="URL" type="ARCURL" maxOccurs="unbounded"/>
            </xsd:sequence>
          </xsd:complexType>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="BartenderURL" type="xsd:anyURI" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="Broker" type="xsd:string" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="CACertificatePath" type="xsd:string" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="CACertificatesDir" type="xsd:string" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="CertificatePath" type="xsd:string" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="CertLifetime" type="xsd:duration" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="Debug" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
              
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
          <xsd:simpleType>
            <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
              <xsd:enumeration value="DEBUG"/>
              <xsd:enumeration value="VERBOSE"/>
              <xsd:enumeration value="INFO"/>
              <xsd:enumeration value="FATAL"/>
              <xsd:enumeration value="ERROR"/>
              <xsd:enumeration value="WARNING"/>
            </xsd:restriction>
          </xsd:simpleType>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="DownloadDir" type="xsd:string" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="IdPname" type="xsd:string" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="JobListFile" type="xsd:string" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="Keep" type="xsd:boolean" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="Keypass" type="xsd:string" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="KeyPath" type="xsd:string" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="Keysize" type="xsd:string" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="Password" type="xsd:string" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="ProxyPath" type="xsd:string" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="SLCSURL" type="xsd:string" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="StoreDir" type="xsd:string" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="TimeOut" type="xsd:duration" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
When communicating over a network the response time, the time from sending a
request and obtaining a response, can vary alot. With the
<element>TimeOut</element> element it is possible to specify how long time
should be spend waiting for a response. If the response time exceeds the
specified timeout ...?
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="UserName" type="xsd:string" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
        <xsd:element name="VOMSServerPath" type="xsd:string" minOccurs="0">
          <xsd:annotation>
            <xsd:documentation>
            </xsd:documentation>
          </xsd:annotation>
        </xsd:element>
      </xsd:all>
    </xsd:complexType>
  </xsd:element>

  <xsd:simpleType name="FlavourEnum">
    <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
      <xsd:enumeration value="ARC0"/>
      <xsd:enumeration value="ARC1"/>
      <xsd:enumeration value="CREAM"/>
      <xsd:enumeration value="UNICORE"/>
    </xsd:restriction>
  </xsd:simpleType>

  <xsd:simpleType name="ServiceTypeEnum">
    <xsd:restriction base="xsd:string">
      <xsd:enumeration value="index"/>
      <xsd:enumeration value="computing"/>
    </xsd:restriction>
  </xsd:simpleType>

  <xsd:element name="URL" maxOccurs="unbounded">
    <xsd:annotation>
      <xsd:documentation>
With the <element>URL</element> element it is possible to specify a URL pointing
to either a computing or index service. The <attribute>Flavour</attribute>
attribute specifies which middleware the URL is pointing to, and the
<attribute>ServiceType</attribute> attribute the service, either computing or
index. Both of these attributes are required.
      </xsd:documentation>
    </xsd:annotation>
    <xsd:complexType>
      <xsd:simpleContent>
        <xsd:extension base="xsd:anyURI">
          <xsd:attribute name="Flavour" type="FlavourEnum" use="required"/>
          <xsd:attribute name="ServiceType" type="ServiceTypeEnum" use="required"/>
        </xsd:extension>
      </xsd:simpleContent>
    </xsd:complexType>
  </xsd:element>
</xsd:schema>
